{"title":"Bugfix review: EOF consume loop","gitnotes":1,"type":"markdown","body":"## What broke\n\nTrailing whitespace after a valid envelope caused `consume()` to advance `pos` past `input.length`, so `peek()` kept returning synthetic tokens.\n\n## Fix tour\n\n1. [EOF guard in consume()](gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/parser/src/tokenizer.ts#R36-R41) — skip advance when `kind === 'eof'`.\n2. [Bounds check in advance()](gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/parser/src/tokenizer.ts#R45-R46) — early `break` at end.\n\n### Before / after (micro-bench, 10k empty consumes)\n\n| | ops/sec |\n|---|--------:|\n| before | hang (∞ loop) |\n| after | ~1.2M |\n\n- [x] Root cause identified\n- [x] Minimal diff (6 lines)\n- [ ] Regression test in commit 06\n\n> **Ship it** — blocking bug for any note with trailing newline + spaces."}
